The five suspects involved in the murder case of former Bafana Bafana captain and Orlando Pirates Striker Senzo Meyiwa have been named. They are Muzikawulahlelwa S’tembu Sibiya, Bongani Sandiso Ntanzi, Mthobisi Prince Mncube, Mthokosizeni Ziphozonke Maphisa and Sifikuhle Nkani Ntuli. JUST IN: Here are the names of the accused in the #SenzoMeyiwa murder case. Muzikawulahlelwa S’tembu Sibiya, Bongani Sandiso Ntanzi, Mthobisi Prince Mncube, Mthokosizeni Ziphozonke Maphisa and Sifikuhle Nkani Ntuli.#sabcnews — Chriselda ‘Babes WeNdaba’ Lewis ™️ (@Chriseldalewis) October 27, 2020  Their charges include murder, attempted murder, robbery with aggravating cirumstances and the illegal possession of a firearm. BREAKING: [WATCH] Magistrate Havenga ALLOWS media to broadcast proceedings. These are the 5 accused. Now LIVE on #SABCNEWS channel 404. pic.twitter.com/udeay9ANbP — Chriselda ‘Babes WeNdaba’ Lewis ™️ (@Chriseldalewis) October 27, 2020  The suspects arrived at the Boksburg Magistrate’s Court east of Johannesburg under heavy police guard and were quickly led into the court. Supporters of the Meyiwa family also gathered outside court. Crowds of onlookers including football supporters waited eagerly outside the court to catch a glimpse of the suspects. Members of AfriForum including former NPA prosecutor Gerrie Nel are present in court. Meyiwa’s brother Sifiso is also present. The suspects were arrested in Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. Meyiwa was shot in front of his girlfriend musician Kelly Khumalo at her home in Vosloorus in 2014. Court proceedings in the Senzo Meyiwa case are being streamed in the video below:  – Reporting by Tshepo Phagane & Melini Moses 